<i>Who were those people</i>

2
00:00:13,644 --> 00:00:18,910
<i>Who won their love?</i>

3
00:00:18,910 --> 00:00:23,980
<i>When obsecrating for rosebuds</i>

4
00:00:23,980 --> 00:00:30,452
<i>I was presented with a garland of thorns...</i>

5
00:00:30,452 --> 00:00:35,964
<i>Who were those people</i>

6
00:00:35,964 --> 00:00:40,669
<i>Who won their love?</i>

7
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:21,055
Ruqaiyya?

8
00:01:21,055 --> 00:01:23,026
What happened?

9
00:01:25,050 --> 00:01:27,070
What happened?

10
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:35,690
Nothing.

11
00:01:35,690 --> 00:01:37,888
Nothing, really.

12
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:48,020
A bite is stuck in my throat.

13
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:51,590
When one's son is nowhere to be seen,

14
00:01:51,590 --> 00:01:56,648
One can't digest the sorrow or the food, Molvi Sahab.

15
00:02:01,820 --> 00:02:03,610
Nor can I, like you,

16
00:02:03,610 --> 00:02:07,049
Defeat grief with sheer will.

17
00:03:37,410 --> 00:03:40,224
Did you offer your prayers?

18
00:03:41,443 --> 00:03:44,160
Did you offer your prayers?

19
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,450
Prayers?

20
00:03:45,450 --> 00:03:49,255
It protects you from upheavals and wards off countless troubles, you blighter!

21
00:03:49,255 --> 00:03:50,258
Get up!

22
00:03:50,258 --> 00:03:51,470
Purify yourself right now,

23
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:54,003
And get yourselves on the prayer mat.

24
00:03:54,003 --> 00:03:56,087
Why did you slap me?

25
00:03:56,087 --> 00:03:58,950
Girls like you are only brought to their senses when slapped!

26
00:03:58,950 --> 00:04:00,156
Offer your prayers, quick!

27
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:02,051
And pray for the well-being of those

28
00:04:02,051 --> 00:04:03,597
Whom you meet,

29
00:04:03,597 --> 00:04:04,980
Or call.

30
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:06,801
What?

31
00:04:07,528 --> 00:04:09,712
While praying today,

32
00:04:09,712 --> 00:04:12,094
My eyes teared up.

33
00:04:12,094 --> 00:04:15,950
I didn't even realise I was weeping!

34
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:17,698
The angels would be laughing at you right now.

35
00:04:17,698 --> 00:04:19,751
Bother about your own -

36
00:04:19,751 --> 00:04:22,937
They listen either to the clinking of your anklets or the sweet melodies of 'I've tasted blood'!

37
00:04:22,937 --> 00:04:25,815
The poor fellows would be sitting with their ears shut!

38
00:04:25,815 --> 00:04:26,650
Get up!

39
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:27,792
Offer your prayers,

40
00:04:27,792 --> 00:04:31,080
So that it relieves the angel on your left shoulder [scribe noting evil deeds].

41
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:33,644
I've heard that when your type finally sits on the prayer mat,

42
00:04:33,644 --> 00:04:36,364
One can hope for an immediate relief!

43
00:04:36,364 --> 00:04:38,543
I don't know why my heart's saying

44
00:04:38,543 --> 00:04:42,128
That you're in need of urgent relief.

45
00:04:42,622 --> 00:04:43,450
Are you getting up,

46
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,110
Or do you want another?

47
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:46,890
I am.

48
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,380
Wait.

49
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:51,946
Just for now,

50
00:04:51,946 --> 00:04:53,505
Take off these anklets for a change.

51
00:04:53,505 --> 00:04:57,889
You don't need this background music in orison!

52
00:05:01,350 --> 00:05:03,312
You hag!

53
00:05:23,180 --> 00:05:25,510
Both the bullets had hit him on the leg, right?

54
00:05:25,510 --> 00:05:26,579
Right...

55
00:05:26,579 --> 00:05:30,080
Then there's nothing to worry about.

56
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,979
Right...

57
00:05:33,759 --> 00:05:35,948
Why aren't the doctors coming out, then?

58
00:05:35,948 --> 00:05:38,883
Why don't they say that everything's fine?

59
00:05:38,883 --> 00:05:40,898
They're busy with the surgery, mun.

60
00:05:40,898 --> 00:05:41,965
Right...

61
00:05:41,965 --> 00:05:43,707
He must be talking?

62
00:05:43,707 --> 00:05:44,824
No...

63
00:05:44,824 --> 00:05:46,091
How'd he talk?

64
00:05:46,091 --> 00:05:49,746
They'd have given him shots to put him to sleep.

65
00:05:49,746 --> 00:05:51,552
It'll take a few hours, now...

66
00:05:51,552 --> 00:05:55,029
He'd only come to after that, right?
-Right...

67
00:06:02,410 --> 00:06:03,641
Where were you?

68
00:06:03,641 --> 00:06:07,000
I mean, where were you when the blighter had come to kill him?

69
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,047
You're at home all day,

70
00:06:09,047 --> 00:06:10,676
But you'd gone for a good night's stroll tonight?

71
00:06:10,676 --> 00:06:12,851
Sit down, everyone's watching...

72
00:06:12,851 --> 00:06:14,210
What? What are they watching?

73
00:06:14,210 --> 00:06:14,956
Look,

74
00:06:14,956 --> 00:06:16,378
Don't change the topic.

75
00:06:16,378 --> 00:06:18,554
Why don't you change the topic?

76
00:06:18,554 --> 00:06:23,169
If you talk and ask about him again and again, they'd ask you who you are to him.

77
00:06:23,169 --> 00:06:24,436
Hey!

78
00:06:24,436 --> 00:06:26,180
I'm his landlady, mun!

79
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:28,107
Hush!

80
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,372
Sit, now.

81
00:06:30,372 --> 00:06:31,451
Enough! C'mon.

82
00:06:31,451 --> 00:06:33,444
Sit down.

83
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:24,610
... Leaves an impression with his humility, my dear.
-Just mention her name and address.

84
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:27,020
I'll talk to Dad.
-Love Farah for four months --

85
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:29,260
What's this balderdash!
-Swear on my life if I'm lying.

86
00:07:29,260 --> 00:07:31,630
Just keep on loving me,
-That's neat.

87
00:07:31,630 --> 00:07:35,230
You're a right emotional man.
-She's just voicing unfounded suspicions!
-The move he's played

88
00:07:35,230 --> 00:07:38,980
Is one I'll never forgive him for!
-What's your wife's name?
-My Afzal has become the best one [Afzal] today!

89
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:41,870
You've just gotten up, haven't you?
-But he's a first rate fraudster.
-Just a spot of lipstick's got you stunned!

90
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:44,130
Then why did you take us there?
-How say you tell me -

91
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:46,150
How does this lipstick look?
-Farah is the one who used to write you letters, right?

92
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:49,670
I'd kept you as an option.
-You'd leave Hyderabad for the one who doesn't love you,

93
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:51,820
Shoot the bugger!
-She's not the one who used to write letters to me, Mum.

94
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:54,430
The job as a security guard, you know...
-And you'd leave those who love you

95
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:56,810
In Hyderabad?
-'My Afzal'

96
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:58,610
'Has become a great man'.
-Spit in my face if I lose.

97
00:07:58,610 --> 00:08:01,990
10,000 a month, and loving Farah Ibrahim!
-Just don't do that

98
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:06,270
Which you would be ashamed to do.
-Proposals will line up once Wali's out of the picture, you'll see!

99
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:09,220
He'd kill me if he got out! What are you waiting for? Shoot the bugger!

100
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:12,079
Afzal!

101
00:09:39,530 --> 00:09:42,020
I've offered my prayers.

102
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,889
Now, beseech the Lord

103
00:09:43,889 --> 00:09:48,053
That he be alright.

104
00:09:48,053 --> 00:09:49,904
Who?

105
00:09:49,904 --> 00:09:52,513
Do I have to tell you his name, now?

106
00:09:52,513 --> 00:09:55,020
His name is etched in every breath of yours

107
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:58,386
And courses through your veins, Lubna.

108
00:09:58,386 --> 00:09:59,757
What happened to him?

109
00:09:59,757 --> 00:10:00,822
There!

110
00:10:00,822 --> 00:10:02,906
Now you know who it is!

111
00:10:02,906 --> 00:10:04,433
Don't worry.

112
00:10:04,433 --> 00:10:06,183
Nothing's happened to him.

113
00:10:06,183 --> 00:10:07,942
I just thought

114
00:10:07,942 --> 00:10:10,455
That may nothing happen to him.

115
00:10:10,455 --> 00:10:12,411
I've prayed for many people,

116
00:10:12,411 --> 00:10:14,377
But when his name came up, I thought

117
00:10:14,377 --> 00:10:19,495
The most effective prayers for him would come from your heart.

118
00:10:21,246 --> 00:10:23,930
What did you think?

119
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:26,786
And why did you think that may nothing happen to him?

120
00:10:26,786 --> 00:10:28,285
Why are you on the rack?

121
00:10:28,285 --> 00:10:30,436
Beseech the Lord if you've already offered you prayers

122
00:10:30,436 --> 00:10:31,419
That

123
00:10:31,419 --> 00:10:33,381
May the Lord will that he be fine.

124
00:10:33,381 --> 00:10:36,253
In fact, you should keep praying for him.

125
00:10:36,253 --> 00:10:37,302
I said it

126
00:10:37,302 --> 00:10:38,552
Because it just occurred to me,

127
00:10:38,552 --> 00:10:39,050
'Alright',

128
00:10:39,050 --> 00:10:40,010
'Offer your prayers',

129
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:42,262
'Beseech the Lord'.

130
00:10:42,262 --> 00:10:44,146
You're hiding something from me, aren't you?

131
00:10:44,146 --> 00:10:45,598
Good Lord!

132
00:10:45,598 --> 00:10:47,978
It seems you'd tear up any moment!

133
00:10:47,978 --> 00:10:50,660
Didn't I just say it's nothing, really?

134
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:52,383
Mum had said once,

135
00:10:52,383 --> 00:10:53,403
'You offer prayers'

136
00:10:53,403 --> 00:10:54,872
'And beseech the Lord'

137
00:10:54,872 --> 00:10:58,086
'The moment you have the slightest of doubt'.

138
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:02,490
What is going on?

139
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:04,562
Nothing, really...

140
00:12:04,562 --> 00:12:08,470
We're both scared, so, for a while,

141
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:10,580
We're avoiding each other's gaze.

142
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:14,221
Why are you scared?

143
00:12:14,221 --> 00:12:18,761
The 'most excellent one' [Afzal] in the eyes of the two of you,

144
00:12:18,761 --> 00:12:24,910
That rapscallion has disappeared from our sights,

145
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:29,970
And her megrims give your mother's heart a painful plight.

146
00:12:29,970 --> 00:12:33,850
If milk spills from the kettle when it's being boiled,

147
00:12:33,850 --> 00:12:35,860
Or an eye blinks,

148
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:41,257
Or this wastrel, this heart beats a tad hard,

149
00:12:41,257 --> 00:12:43,047
She gets scared.

150
00:12:43,047 --> 00:12:46,280
But you're scared too.

151
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:48,908
Out of respect, yes.

152
00:12:48,908 --> 00:12:51,560
I've heard

153
00:12:51,560 --> 00:12:54,710
'Ordinary people should be scared'

154
00:12:54,710 --> 00:12:59,919
'When a mother gets scared'.

155
00:13:02,939 --> 00:13:04,809
Alright, Ruqaiyya,

156
00:13:04,809 --> 00:13:10,280
I've decided to sleep peacefully until dawn.

157
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,813
Stop telling your rosary,

158
00:13:12,813 --> 00:13:17,824
And chant a hymn to get me sleepy.

159
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:34,720
He's alright now.

160
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,556
He's talking, isn't he?

161
00:13:36,556 --> 00:13:37,840
He's unconscious right now, sir.

162
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:40,409
When he'd come to in the morning, he'd be talking, too.

163
00:13:40,409 --> 00:13:42,430
Excuse me.

164
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:45,552
There! That's all it ever was. He's alright now.

165
00:13:45,552 --> 00:13:46,941
Let's get going, then.

166
00:13:46,941 --> 00:13:48,361
Going?

167
00:13:48,361 --> 00:13:51,200
Call me if you need anything.

168
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,008
You'll get it.

169
00:13:53,008 --> 00:13:54,230
C'mon, now.

170
00:13:54,230 --> 00:13:57,220
Mam, how could we just leave like that? The poor man's just come to!

171
00:13:57,220 --> 00:13:57,860
Just come!

172
00:13:57,860 --> 00:14:03,268
Very bad, Mam! We should be staying here, how -- Mam, how could we just leave?
-Everyone's watching you!

173
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,421
Okay.

174
00:14:19,421 --> 00:14:21,740
God be with ye.
-God be with ye.

175
00:14:24,430 --> 00:14:25,719
Is Farah coming along?

176
00:14:25,719 --> 00:14:27,524
No? Why would she?

177
00:14:27,524 --> 00:14:29,606
But she's in the car!

